Lineup Core: Mai Chiyo, Volt Blaster\nIdeal for beginners, this lineup is versatile in battle and compatible with any weapon, providing strong performance. It forms quickly and has a high tolerance for errors.

Lineup Core: Makluba The Wise, Arkhan Frosthand\nIn battle, it adapts to the Light & Dark weapon, which evolved from T1 Priest weapon. The Light & Dark weapon provides significant buffs when the hero's HP changes frequently. Makluba The Wise's skill drains HP from all while healing all, quickly gaining Light & Dark benefits. Makluba The Wise, Arkhan Frosthand, and Mai Chiyo also benefit from the Light & Dark weapon. When the hero reaches 8★, they will receive additional benefits from the Light & Dark weapon in battle.

Lineup Core: Calliope, Peckaruto\nIn battle, it adapts to the Reload weapon, which evolved from T1 Marksman weapon. Heroes equipped with the Reload weapon have a special charge attack mode at 6★, dealing higher damage with additional effects after a short period of inactivity, resulting in substantial burst damage. Calliope, Peckaruto, and Volt Blaster will receive additional benefits from the Reload weapon in battle when they reach 8★.

Lineup Core: C-Ken Walker, Perry Hotwings\nIn battle, it adapts to the Rage weapon, which evolved from T1 Mage weapon. Upon obtaining the Rage weapon, the hero's ASPD is increased and additional damage buffs are gained. C-Ken Walker and Perry Hotwings' attacks have a chance to trigger special effects. When the hero reaches 8★, they will receive additional benefits from the Rage weapon in battle.

Lineup Core: Monty Holden, Blind Hunter\nIn battle, it adapts to the Bleed weapon, which evolved from T1 Assassin weapon. The Bleed weapon inflicts debuff Bleed on enemy units. Paired with Monty Holden, who can deal split attacks, Blind Hunter can inflict more frequent damage on targets. When the hero reaches 8★, they will receive additional benefits from the Bleed weapon in battle.

Lineup Core: Cluckbuster, Mind Broiler\nIn battle, it adapts to the Heavy Strike weapon, which evolved from T1 Warrior weapon. The Heavy Strike weapon can increase the damage caused by heavy strikes, matching perfectly with the high-frequency heavy strikes of Cluckbuster and Mind Broiler. Upon reaching 8★, the hero will also enjoy additional benefits from the Heavy Strike weapon in battle.

Lineup Core: Clustercluck, Wonder Fowl, Ghostplume\nIn this ultimate lineup, Clustercluck and Ghostplume have superior AOE capabilities, quickly clearing all enemies. Additionally, high-star Clustercluck and Wonder Fowl both have a chance to not consume attack times, providing even more powerful and sustained damage.
